cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SI 

The paper deals with the problem of learning-to-learn, which is a core topic in machine learning. The use of Stochastic Gradient Descent (SGD) and regularization techniques makes it relevant to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the estimation of bias from a sequence of tasks, which is related to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of regularization techniques in the context of computer vision tasks makes it relevant to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the learning ability of the meta-algorithm, which is related to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper proposes a low space and time complexity approach, which is related to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
